{{! /freestyle/records — per-trick consecutive records }}

<div class="hero hero-sm">
  <div>
    {{#if navigation.breadcrumbs}}
    <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      {{#each navigation.breadcrumbs}}
        {{#if href}}<a href="{{href}}">{{label}}</a> <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span> {{else}}<span>{{label}}</span>{{/if}}
      {{/each}}
    </nav>
    {{/if}}
    <h1>{{page.title}}</h1>
    {{#if page.intro}}<p class="hero-subtitle">{{page.intro}}</p>{{/if}}
  </div>
</div>

<div class="wrapper">

  <p>
    A consecutive record is the most times a player has landed a single
    trick in a row without a miss. It is a test of focus and endurance as
    much as skill. The records below are the documented bests, grouped by
    type.
  </p>

  <p class="text-muted fs-sm">
    ADD (recorded) is the difficulty the recording source assigned when each
    record was logged. Where it differs from a trick's canonical ADD on its
    detail page, the canonical ADD is authoritative. For how canonical ADD is
    counted, see <a href="/freestyle/add-analysis">ADD Accounting &amp; Analysis</a>.
  </p>

  {{#if content.hasUnlinkedRecords}}
  <p class="text-muted fs-sm">
    A few of these record names come from older sources and do not match a
    trick in the current dictionary, so those names are shown without a link.
  </p>
  {{/if}}

  {{#if content.groups}}
    {{#each content.groups}}
    <section class="records-group">
      <h2 class="section-heading">{{label}}</h2>

      <div class="records-table-wrap">
        <table class="records-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Trick</th>
              <th>ADD (recorded)</th>
              <th class="col-num">Count</th>
              <th>Holder</th>
              <th>Date</th>
              <th>Video</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {{#each records}}
            <tr>
              <td>
                {{#if trickHref}}
                  <a href="{{trickHref}}" class="trick-name">{{trickName}}</a>
                {{else}}
                  <span class="trick-name">{{trickName}}</span>
                {{/if}}
                {{#if sortName}}
                <span class="trick-sort-name">{{sortName}}</span>
                {{/if}}
              </td>
              <td class="col-adds">
                {{#if addsCount}}{{addsCount}}{{else}}&mdash;{{/if}}
              </td>
              <td class="col-num">{{valueNumeric}}</td>
              <td class="col-holder">
                {{#if holderHref}}
                  <a href="{{holderHref}}">{{holderName}}</a>
                {{else}}
                  {{holderName}}
                {{/if}}
              </td>
              <td class="col-date">
                {{#if achievedDate}}
                  {{formatDate achievedDate}}{{#if dateApproximate}} <em>(approx.)</em>{{/if}}
                {{else}}
                  &mdash;
                {{/if}}
              </td>
              <td>
                {{#if videoUrl}}
                  <a href="{{videoUrl}}" class="video-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
                     aria-label="Watch {{holderName}} {{trickName}} record video">
                    ▶{{#if videoTimecode}} {{videoTimecode}}{{/if}}
                  </a>
                {{else}}
                  &mdash;
                {{/if}}
              </td>
            </tr>
            {{/each}}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

    </section>
    {{/each}}
  {{else}}
  <div class="empty-state">No records found.</div>
  {{/if}}

  <p class="source-note">
    These records are drawn from documented freestyle video archives and
    community tracking; historical coverage is incomplete and keeps growing.
    Dates marked <em>approx.</em> are confirmed only to the month or year,
    and records shown with a disclaimer are probable but not independently
    verified.
  </p>

</div>
